Some more thoughts I have about this are other top players DQ'ing:

I get that there's unavoidable situations that forces you to DQ.

But in other times where you DQ because you feel off and/or poor planning is truly some of the most disappointing shit a top player can do

It's disappointing because part of being a top player to me is competing even when things are against your favor, and when you DQ because things didnt go your way, you are robbing yourself opportunities to learn from that experience, because chances are it will pop up again.

It's disappointing to the viewers excited to watch you, it's directly hurting TO's that marketed and invested in you to compete, it fucks up the bracket so it becomes very unfair, and it makes the storyline of the tournament all the more lesser. It impacts everyone.

And if the reasoning to DQ is because of some ego shit about seeding, you don't feel 100%, feeling depressed after losing, your scheduling sucks, things that are tangibly in your control, that is just disappointing that your reasoning to DQ can be prevented if you just Grow. Up.
